I"S<p>Following the links on <a href="https://github.com/dommmel/jekyll-youtube">this page</a>, I added a plugin to embed a YouTube video in my posts.</p>

<p>So let’s test it.</p>

<p>First, here’s an example of how to embed a video of the <a href="https://www.discogs.com/Lucifers-Friend-Lucifers-Friend/master/90119">Lucifer’s Friend</a> album I gave a run today:</p>

<pre><style>.embed-container { position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; max-width: 100%; } .embed-container iframe, .embed-container object, .embed-container embed { position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; }</style><div class="embed-container">    <iframe title="YouTube video player" width="640" height="390" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/-y9AJ4HVAQg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></pre>

<p>And if all goes well, the video should be embedded below:</p>

<style>.embed-container { position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; max-width: 100%; } .embed-container iframe, .embed-container object, .embed-container embed { position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; }</style>
<div class="embed-container">    <iframe title="YouTube video player" width="640" height="390" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/-y9AJ4HVAQg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div>

